. </p>
<p>

Notably, he openly used his songwriting for political purposes, especially against the then-current apartheid regime of <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../221/17416221.xml">
South Africa</link></country>
. <musical_organization wordnetid="108246613" confidence="0.8">
<group wordnetid="100031264" confidence="0.8">
<quartet wordnetid="108247251" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../423/30423.xml">
The Clash</link></quartet>
</group>
</musical_organization>
 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../230/2417230.xml">
recorded</link> a version of "Police on My Back" for their <it><album wordnetid="106591815" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../650/596650.xml">
Sandinista!</link></album>
</it> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../185/2238185.xml">
triple album</link>.</p>
<p>

Later, Grant shifted his focus to Ice Records, and began reissuing recordings by <music_genre wordnetid="107071942" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../175/154175.xml">
calypso</link></music_genre>
